The paper deals with the K-user interference channel with secrecy constraints, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed scheme involves the use of artificial noises to ensure confidentiality, which is a technique commonly used in network coding (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multiple rounds of transmission, which is a technique used in multimedia communication (cs.MM).
